:::summary
Gardening is the practice of cultivating plants — vegetables, fruits, herbs, flowers, and trees — for food, beauty, medicine, and spiritual renewal. From the Garden of Eden to the monastic gardens of medieval Europe and the kitchen gardens of American homesteads, tending the earth has always been close to the heart of human civilization. Gardening connects us to the rhythms of creation, teaches patience and stewardship, and provides some of the most honest labor and wholesome reward available to any person.
:::

